# Project Contract

## Build And Test

### Frontend
- Install: `{{pm}} install`
- Dev: `{{pm}} {{run}}dev`
- Build: `{{pm}} {{run}}build`
- Test: `{{pm}} {{run}}test`
- Typecheck: `{{pm}} {{run}}type-check`
- Lint: `{{pm}} {{run}}lint`

### Backend
- Build: `mvn clean package -DskipTests`
- Test: `mvn test`
- Run: `mvn spring-boot:run`
- Check: `mvn compile`

## Architecture Boundaries

### Frontend
- Pages/Views: `src/views/`
- Components: `src/components/` (common: `src/components/common/`)
- State management: `src/stores/` (Pinia)
- API calls: `src/api/` — do not call backend directly from components
- Router: `src/router/`
- Types: `src/types/`

### Backend
- Controller: `src/main/java/**/controller/` — parameter validation + call Service only
- Service: `src/main/java/**/service/` — business logic
- Repository/Mapper: `src/main/java/**/mapper/` — data access
- Entity/Model: `src/main/java/**/entity/`
- Config: `src/main/java/**/config/` — Spring configuration

## Coding Conventions

### Frontend
- Vue 3 Composition API + `<script setup>` syntax
- Pinia for state, avoid Vuex
- TypeScript strict mode where applicable
- Component naming: PascalCase for files and usage
- Composables in `src/composables/`, prefix with `use`

### Backend
- Java naming: camelCase methods, PascalCase classes, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE constants
- RESTful API design, uniform response wrapper
- Use Lombok `@Data` / `@Builder` for DTOs
- Exceptions through global handler, not per-controller try-catch

{{safety-rails}}

### Stack-specific NEVER
- Modify `application-prod.yml` or `application-prod.properties` without explicit approval
- Commit without running frontend lint and backend compile
- Change database migration files after they have been applied
- Expose internal service errors directly to API responses

### Stack-specific ALWAYS
- Run frontend typecheck + lint before marking task done
- Run backend compile (`mvn compile`) after Java edits
- Add appropriate null checks in Java code

## Verification
- Frontend changes: `pnpm typecheck` + `pnpm lint` + `pnpm test`
- Backend changes: `mvn compile` + `mvn test`
- API changes: update API docs and contract tests
- Database changes: verify migration up and down
- UI changes: capture before/after screenshots

